From e442d29f7b4b9867b415fb4f894cb520b0ceb7b8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 13:24:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 10 Batch 1: review draft service +
 Start/Continue/Submit/Discard

Replace the PR header's Check Out button with a state-aware review-mode
button: Start Review (no draft) / Continue Review (draft, not on head)
/ Submit Review (draft, on head). A Discard button surfaces alongside
once a draft exists.

- New IKrtReviewDraftService persists per-PR drafts under
  krt.reviewDrafts.v1. Comments accumulate locally and post to GitHub
  via a new IPullRequestProvider.submitReview(url, submission) that
  POSTs /repos/{o}/{r}/pulls/{n}/reviews with the full batch.
- KrtPrCommentController consults the draft service in submitNewComment:
  when a draft exists for the PR, the new comment is added to the draft
  instead of being posted immediately. refreshUri merges pending draft
  comments alongside server-side ones with a "Pending" label so they
  render in place inside the inline thread.
- Discard runs the existing Phase 8.7 returnFrom flow when KRT owns
  the active resume token, returning the workspace to its previous
  state. Submit invalidates the cache and reloads review comments so
  the freshly-posted batch appears as native (non-pending) threads.
